# GitHub Packages auth for the @nehoupat scope. Copy this file to .npmrc
# (.npmrc is in .gitignore - never commit it, it contains your token).
#
# 1) Get a GitHub Personal Access Token (PAT) with `read:packages` scope from
#    your dearmarc subscription. The PAT is valid for 1 year (or per your
#    subscription terms).
#
# 2) Copy this file: cp .npmrc.example .npmrc
#
# 3) Either replace ${GITHUB_TOKEN} below with the literal token value, OR
#    export it as an env variable before running `npm install`:
#       export GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxxx
#
# 4) On expiry, you renew via a new PAT from dearmarc. Your existing deploy
#    keeps running - only `npm install` will fail until you have a valid token.

@nehoupat:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com
//npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=${GITHUB_TOKEN}
